+## Class: WebSocket
+
+> Intercept and handle WebSocket connections created by pages and workers in a
+> session.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)<br />
+_This class is not exported from the `'electron'` module. It is only available
+as a property of a [`Session`](session.md) instance._
+
+Instances of the `WebSocket` class are accessed by using the `webSocket`
+property of a `Session`.
+
+### Instance Methods
+
+#### `webSocket.setHandler([filter, ]handler)`
+
+* `filter` [WebSocketFilter](structures/web-socket-filter.md) (optional)
+* `handler` Function | null
+  * `socket` [WebSocketMain](#class-websocketmain)
+
+Sets the handler used to intercept matching WebSocket connections. Passing
+`null` removes the handler.
+
+Only one handler can be active for a session. If no handler is set, or if the
+URL does not match the filter, Electron continues with its default WebSocket
+handling.
+
+The connection stays pending until the handler calls one of
+[`socket.continue()`](#socketcontinue),
+[`socket.accept([options])`](#socketacceptoptions), or
+[`socket.fail([reason])`](#socketfailreason). The decision can be made
+asynchronously after the handler returns.
+
+```js
+const { session } = require('electron')
+
+session.defaultSession.webSocket.setHandler(
+  { urls: ['ws://127.0.0.1:*/*'] },
+  async (socket) => {
+    socket.accept()
+    await socket.send('hello from main')
+  }
+)
+```
+
+## Class: WebSocketMain
+
+> Represents one intercepted WebSocket connection.
+
+Process: [Main](../glossary.md#main-process)<br />
+_This class is not exported from the `'electron'` module. It is only available
+as the argument passed to
+[`webSocket.setHandler([filter, ]handler)`](#websocketsethandlerfilter-handler)._
+
+### Instance Events
+
+#### Event: 'message'
+
+Returns:
+
+* `message` [WebSocketMessage](structures/web-socket-message.md)
+
+Emitted when the renderer sends a WebSocket message to the accepted connection.
+
+#### Event: 'close'
+
+Returns:
+
+* `details` [WebSocketCloseDetails](structures/web-socket-close-details.md)
+
+Emitted when the renderer starts closing the WebSocket or when the connection is
+destroyed.
+
+### Instance Methods
+
+#### `socket.continue()`
+
+Continues the connection through Electron's default WebSocket handling. This
+preserves the existing [`webRequest`](web-request.md), extension, and Chromium
+network behavior.
+
+#### `socket.accept([options])`
+
+* `options` [WebSocketAcceptOptions](structures/web-socket-accept-options.md) (optional)
+
+Accepts the connection in the main process.
+
+#### `socket.fail([reason])`
+
+* `reason` string (optional)
+
+Fails the connection. If the connection has already been accepted, the renderer
+observes an abnormal close.
+
+#### `socket.send(message)`
+
+* `message` string | Buffer | [WebSocketMessage](structures/web-socket-message.md)
+
+Returns `Promise<void>` - Resolves after the message has been queued to the
+renderer.
+
+Sends a message to the renderer side of the accepted WebSocket.
+
+#### `socket.close([code, reason])`
+
+* `code` Integer (optional) - Defaults to `1000`.
+* `reason` string (optional)
+
+Closes the accepted WebSocket.
+
+#### `socket.pause()`
+
+Pauses incoming renderer-to-main message delivery.
+
+#### `socket.resume()`
+
+Resumes incoming renderer-to-main message delivery.
+
+#### `socket.isDestroyed()`
+
+Returns `boolean` - Whether the WebSocket connection has been destroyed.
+
+### Instance Properties
+
+#### `socket.id` _Readonly_
+
+A `string` identifying this WebSocket connection.
+
+#### `socket.url` _Readonly_
+
+A `string` containing the WebSocket URL.
+
+#### `socket.protocols` _Readonly_
+
+A `string[]` containing the subprotocols requested by the renderer.
+
+#### `socket.creatorType` _Readonly_
+
+A `string` identifying the object that created the WebSocket. Can be `frame`,
+`dedicated-worker`, `shared-worker`, `service-worker` or `unknown`.
+
+#### `socket.creator` _Readonly_
+
+A `WebFrameMain | DedicatedWorkerMain | SharedWorkerMain | ServiceWorkerMain | null`
+identifying the object that created the WebSocket.
+
+#### `socket.bufferedAmount` _Readonly_
+
+An `Integer` indicating the number of bytes queued by
+[`socket.send(message)`](#socketsendmessage) and not yet written to the
+renderer.
